<!-- ═══ CHALLENGE ═══ -->
<section class="cs-section">
  <div class="cs-section-inner reveal">
    <h2 class="cs-section-heading">THE CHALLENGE</h2>
    <div class="cs-body">
      <p>ZAR's product was built by freelancers. Multiple designers, multiple engineers, no shared system, no shared language. The Figma files were a graveyard of duplicated components, orphaned frames, and styles that varied by who designed them and when. Every screen looked slightly different.</p>
      <p>The product spanned three platforms — iOS, Android, and web — each with its own visual inconsistencies. Engineers had no reliable source of truth for design specifications. Every feature handoff was a negotiation: "Which version of this button do I use? What's the correct spacing? Is this the right shade of gray?"</p>
      <p>To make it harder, the product itself was evolving rapidly. ZAR pivoted its positioning multiple times, which meant the design system couldn't be a static artifact — it had to keep pace with a moving target.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ METRIC HIGHLIGHT ═══ -->
<div class="cs-highlight">
  <div class="cs-highlight-inner reveal">
    <span class="cs-highlight-value">670+</span>
