</section>

<!-- ═══ SOLUTION ═══ -->
<section class="cs-section">
  <div class="cs-section-inner reveal">
    <h2 class="cs-section-heading">THE SOLUTION</h2>
    <div class="cs-body">
      <p>Techtonic in its final form was a comprehensive multi-platform design system. 670+ components spanning iOS, Android, and web. 103 custom icons. Design tokens managed in Figma and synced to GitHub. Storybook documentation for engineering self-service. 37 organized Figma pages covering primitives, patterns, templates, and platform-specific adaptations.</p>
      <p>The system was designed for engineer self-service. Component documentation included not just visual specs but behavior descriptions, state management guidelines, and accessibility requirements. An engineer could pick up a component from Storybook and implement it without needing a designer in the room.</p>
      <p>Token architecture followed a three-tier model: primitive tokens (raw values), semantic tokens (contextual meaning), and component tokens (specific to individual components). This gave the system both flexibility and specificity.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cs-img-placeholder cs-img-placeholder--lg">
      <i class="ph-bold ph-image"></i>
      <span>Add screenshot — Techtonic design system overview</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ IMPACT ═══ -->
<section class="cs-section">
  <div class="cs-section-inner reveal">
    <h2 class="cs-section-heading">THE IMPACT</h2>
    <div class="cs-impact-grid">
      <div class="cs-impact-stat">
        <span class="cs-impact-val">670+</span>
        <span class="cs-impact-label">Components</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-impact-stat">
        <span class="cs-impact-val">37</span>
        <span class="cs-impact-label">Figma pages</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-impact-stat">
        <span class="cs-impact-val">103</span>
        <span class="cs-impact-label">Custom icons</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-impact-stat">
        <span class="cs-impact-val">3</span>
        <span class="cs-impact-label">Platforms</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="cs-body">
      <p>Techtonic transformed ZAR's development workflow. Engineers stopped waiting for designers to hand off specs — they could self-serve from Storybook. Design reviews shifted from "does this match the design?" to "does this solve the user problem?" — a much more valuable conversation.</p>
      <p>The three-time rebuild was actually an advantage. Each version incorporated lessons from the last, and the final system was battle-tested against real product changes. It wasn't theoretical — it was proven to survive pivots.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

